&lt;p&gt;You know the moment: lights warm the shop, coffee’s cooling on the bench, and the orbital whirs up to speed. You’ve got a cabinet door you’ve already milled true on the jointer, cauls, and clamps. It should be easy land for a quick, clean final prep. But the sander skates differently today—just a hair off, a faint wobble you can feel more than see. Ten minutes later, you hold the piece edgewise to the light and the truth glares back: a bright ring near the panel’s perimeter and a dish in the center. Flatness got away from you. I’ve been there more than once, and I’ve learned the culprit isn’t always the abrasive or your technique. Sometimes it’s the pad itself—or the sander interface pad riding on top—that’s quietly steering your results.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/21.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/27/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/inspect-pad-wear-to-maintain-flatness-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Switch Pads When Moving Up In Grit</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Feb 2026 17:21:43 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-240</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><category>dry sanding</category><description>Engineer-tested guide to switching pads as you move up grits. Choose the right sander interface pad, reduce heat, and improve finish quality.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="sander-interface-pad-when-to-switch-as-grit-climbs"&gt;Sander Interface Pad: When to Switch as Grit Climbs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The radio’s low murmur blends with the scratch-scratch cadence of your sander as you chase a perfect satin surface on a maple tabletop. You can smell resin warming, see dust spiraling in the shaft of afternoon light, feel the sander skate just a bit too eagerly on the flat. The corners are a different story—sharp yesterday, now slightly softened—while the field shows faint halos that only appear when you tilt your head and squint. You pause, run a hand across the grain, and decide to climb from P120 to P180. Instinct says just swap discs and keep going. Experience says this is where surfaces are made or marred. The missing decision? Which pad to put between your machine and the abrasive—specifically, whether to add a sander interface pad, and how to change pad stiffness as you move up in grit.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/05.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/09/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/switch-pads-when-moving-up-in-grit-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Match Pad Hole Pattern To Disc For Suction</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 22 Jan 2026 13:53:36 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-360</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Match pad and disc hole patterns for peak suction. Choose the right sander interface pad, dial airflow, and refine your sanding workflow for flawless finishes.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="optimize-dust-extraction-with-a-sander-interface-pad"&gt;Optimize Dust Extraction with a Sander Interface Pad&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The morning a project turns from anxious to assured often starts with a small decision. You roll up the shop door, the air still cool, and stare at a tabletop whose grain promises more than your last pass delivered. Yesterday, dust swirled despite the extractor, paper loaded early, and faint swirl marks telegraphed through the finish like regrets. Today you commit to variables you can actually control: matching the pad’s hole pattern to your abrasive disc, adjusting your extractor, and adding a purpose-built sander interface pad to tune contact pressure and airflow. The hum of the sander builds; the extractor throttles on; a faint draft kisses the work surface through the perforations. You feel the pad land—not slap—against the wood, compliant enough to fold into crowns and edges but firm enough to maintain a flat across panels.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/18.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/22/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/match-pad-hole-pattern-to-disc-for-suction-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Prevent Edge Burn Through With Softer Pads</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 2026 15:51:09 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-180</category><category>dry sanding</category><category>orbital sander</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Learn how a sander interface pad and softer foams prevent edge burn-through, smooth curves, and reduce swirl for cleaner, faster finishing.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="sander-interface-pad-stop-edge-burn-through"&gt;Sander Interface Pad: Stop Edge Burn-Through&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s a moment in every refinishing project when you hold your breath: that last pass along a fragile edge. Maybe it’s the rounded lip of a vintage table, the chamfer on a cabinet door, or the bead detail on a banister. You’re almost done, the dust looks light, and then—too late—you see it. A pale halo where the finish burned through to bare wood. It’s a small mistake with big consequences: extra patching, uneven stain absorption, and the sinking feeling that you’ve traded progress for rework. If you’ve been there, know this: control is possible, and a simple swap in your setup can save those edges. A sander interface pad gives your sander a softer touch, spreading pressure, hugging contours, and keeping your finish intact where it’s most vulnerable.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/02.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/01/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/prevent-edge-burn-through-with-softer-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>10</readingTime></item><item><title>Multi Density Pad Stacks For Tricky Shapes</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 12 Dec 2025 16:15:21 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>orbital sander</category><description>Learn how to build multi-density sander interface pad stacks for tricky shapes, with step-by-step setups, pro tips, and real-world sanding techniques.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="multi-density-sander-interface-pad-stacks-for-curves"&gt;Multi-Density Sander Interface Pad Stacks for Curves&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first time you chase a graceful curve with a flat sanding disc, you feel it: that tiny chatter, the scratch that won’t blend out, the edge that suddenly burns through. It’s a lesson every builder learns, whether you’re shaping a guitar heel, blending autobody filler into a wheel arch, or easing a bullnose on oak treads. In my shop, those moments used to slow projects to a crawl—especially when my random orbital insisted on flattening what I needed to caress. Then I started stacking foam like a chef layers flavors: soft for drape, medium for control, thin for crispness. That stack, centered on a sander interface pad, turned my sander into a shape-following tool instead of a shape-fighting one.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/15.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/12/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/multi-density-pad-stacks-for-tricky-shapes-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Use Hard Backing Pads For Flat Panels</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 27 Nov 2025 14:34:47 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-360</category><category>paint prep</category><description>Get pro-flat panels with hard backing pads. Learn when a sander interface pad helps, when it hurts, and how to sand dead flat without waves or swirls.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="hard-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad-guide"&gt;Hard Pads for Flat Panels: Sander Interface Pad Guide&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s a certain hush that falls over the shop when a panel finally reads flat. The lights reflect in a clean, uninterrupted glide across the grain, and you can feel the promise of that finish under your fingertips. I remember a maple tabletop that fought me for three late nights. I had a soft pad on my sander, a foam disc, and the hope that “gentle” would keep me safe. Instead, the board smiled back at me with a washboard of highs and lows. Swirls near the edges, dipped corners, and a telegraphed glue line that wouldn’t die. The fix wasn’t more time; it was the right pad. I swapped to a hard backing pad, parked a sander interface pad for the profiles and inside corners, and the surface transformed—crisp, even, and ready to finish. That day, I stopped thinking of pads as accessories and started treating them like cutting tools.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/01.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Follow Contours With Foam Interface Pads</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 15 Nov 2025 13:28:35 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-240</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><category>clear coat</category><category>wet sanding</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Engineer-tested guide to sander interface pads: foam science, thickness choices, test data, and techniques for flawless curves and edges.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="sander-interface-pad-guide-follow-contours-better"&gt;Sander interface pad guide: follow contours better&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first time I tried to refinish a vintage guitar body with tight belly cuts and arm contours, I did what most of us do: I slapped a fresh disc on my random-orbit sander and went to town. Ten minutes in, the color had evened out, but the edges told a different story—flat spots where the soft curve should have been, and a constellation of pigtails where the disc burped dust across a ridge. I stopped, frustrated. This wasn’t a flat tabletop; this was a compound curve. The tool I had was fighting the surface I wanted. That project is when a mentor handed me a simple piece of foam: a sander interface pad.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/14.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/15/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/follow-contours-with-foam-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Reduce Swirls By Pairing Pad And Grit Correctly</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 06 Nov 2025 13:34:29 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-60</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-240</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><description>Learn how pairing a sander interface pad with the right grits reduces swirls, improves cut control, and optimizes dust extraction for flawless finishes.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="mastering-the-sander-interface-pad-to-erase-swirls"&gt;Mastering the sander interface pad to erase swirls&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It always shows up under raking light. You sweep your flashlight across a freshly primed cabinet door or a leveled epoxy table top, and there it is—faint haloing, tight hook-shaped pigtails, and a dull gray cast that just shouldn’t be there. You did the steps. You stepped up the grits. You vacuumed between passes. But the surface still whispers “machine marks.” The moment feels familiar to anyone chasing a clean finish on wood, primer, or clear coat. The fix isn’t more pressure, more passes, or a magic abrasive. It’s control—control of contact pressure, compliance, and cut geometry. And that’s exactly what a sander interface pad delivers when paired correctly with grit and machine settings.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/06/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/reduce-swirls-by-pairing-pad-and-grit-correctly-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>10</readingTime></item><item><title>When To Use Soft Versus Firm Interface Pads</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 03 Nov 2025 05:14:43 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-240</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><category>clear coat</category><description>Learn when to use soft vs firm sander interface pads for smoother finishes, faster leveling, and fewer defects across woodworking and auto refinishing.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="soft-vs-firm-sander-interface-pad-when-to-choose"&gt;Soft vs Firm Sander Interface Pad: When to Choose&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It starts with dust floating in the morning light and a project that matters. Maybe it’s a maple dresser you’ve promised to refinish before the baby arrives, or a fender blend on a car that’s taken you months to prep. Your sander hums to life, and the first pass feels promising—until you notice faint scratches where the grain curves, or a rounded edge where you wanted a crisp line. The tool didn’t change. The abrasive didn’t change. The difference is the cushion between them: the sander interface pad. It’s a small layer, but it decides how much pressure reaches the surface, how evenly the grit cuts, and whether the final result shows craftsmanship or compromise.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/pinterest/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/03/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/when-to-use-soft-versus-firm-interface-pads-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item></channel></rss>